# Backend (.NET 10)

## Layer boundaries

- **Domain** — entities, enums, invariants (no dependencies)
- **Application** — DTOs, FluentValidation, service interfaces, use cases
- **Infrastructure** — EF Core, Identity, service implementations, migrations
- **Api** — thin controllers, middleware, auth attributes

`TreatWarningsAsErrors` is on — fix warnings. Add NuGet versions in `Directory.Packages.props` only.

## Controllers

```csharp
// ✅ Thin controller — logic in Application service
[HttpPost("{id:guid}/post")]
public async Task<ActionResult<InvoiceDto>> Post(Guid id, CancellationToken ct)
    => Ok(await invoicing.PostAsync(id, ct));

// ❌ Business logic, EF queries, or validation in controller
```

- Apply `[Authorize]`, role policies, and `[RequireModule(...)]`
- Document lifecycle: `POST .../{id}/post`, `POST .../{id}/void` per [docs/api/conventions.md](docs/api/conventions.md)
- Use `IDivisionScopeService` for division-scoped queries and writes
- List endpoints return `PagedResult<T>` with normalized page/pageSize

## Application layer

- DTOs + validators colocated under `Jaza.Application/{Module}/`
- `ValidateAndThrowAsync()` before persistence
- Complex logic → interface in Application, implementation in Infrastructure

## Database changes

```powershell
dotnet ef migrations add Name --project src/Jaza.Infrastructure --startup-project src/Jaza.Api
```

## Tests

- Unit: `backend/tests/Jaza.Application.Tests/`
- Integration: `backend/tests/Jaza.Api.IntegrationTests/` — Testcontainers PostgreSQL (**Docker required**)
